text.tspan: Total COVID-19 tests per 1,000 vs. GDP per capita
GDP per capita is adjusted for price differences between countries (it is expressed in international dollars).
Comparisons across countries are affected by differences in testing policies and reporting methods.
Source: Official data collated by Our World in Data; World Bank
Note: Our data on COVID-19 tests and positive rate is no longer updated since 23 June 2022.
